# Datasole Project Rules

## Quality Gate

`npm run gate` is the developer gate. It runs:
format:check ŌåÆ lint ŌåÆ build(all packages) ŌåÆ unit tests + coverage ŌåÆ integration/demo e2e ŌåÆ core e2e ŌåÆ gate:summary

`npm run gate:full` is the exhaustive CI/nightly gate. It adds:
benchmarks ŌåÆ collect-metrics ŌåÆ docs:build

**Run `npm run gate` after making changes.** It is enforced by:
- pre-commit hook: `lint-staged` + `npm run gate`
- pre-push hook: `npm run gate`
- CI/nightly: `npm run gate:full`

`npm run dist` is an alias for `npm run gate`.

## Documentation

Canonical documentation lives in `docs/`. Consult before making structural changes:
- `docs/tutorials.md` ŌĆö Progressive learning examples (update when adding user-facing features)
- `docs/examples.md` ŌĆö Copy-paste recipes by pattern
- `docs/architecture.md` ŌĆö System design, wire protocol
- `docs/decisions.md` ŌĆö Architecture Decision Records
- `docs/contributing.md` ŌĆö Build commands, workflow

## Architecture Decisions

All ADRs in `docs/decisions.md`. When changing deps, protocol, build, transport, state sync, adapters, public API, or the quality gate pipeline: check existing ADRs, add new ones if needed, reference in commit messages.

## Commit Messages

- Start the title with the intent behind the change, not just the files touched
- Use this body format:
  1. 2-3 short lines summarizing the intent behind the commit
  2. 1-5 brief bullet points describing the concrete changes
  3. if the commit adds new features, options, or capabilities, a separate section calling them out
- The intent summary should explain why the change exists, using session context, user goals, bugs, regressions, ADRs, or workflow constraints as evidence
- Generated-artifact or bot commits should still explain intent (`publish verified artifacts`, `publish verified nightly upgrades`), not just `update files`

## Code Organization

- `src/shared/` ŌĆö Zero-dep code shared between client/server (includes CRDTs)
- `src/client/` ŌĆö Browser library (no Node.js APIs)
- `src/server/` ŌĆö Node.js library (may use Node builtins)
- Dependency direction: shared ŌåÉ client, shared ŌåÉ server. No clientŌåöserver imports.

## Build Constants

`src/shared/build-constants.ts` is the single source of truth for version, protocol version, and defaults. Never hardcode these values elsewhere.

## Changelog

Update `CHANGELOG.md` (Keep a Changelog format) when bumping `package.json` version. Group under Added/Changed/Deprecated/Removed/Fixed/Security. Use SemVer: major = breaking, minor = features, patch = fixes.

## Type Safety

- No `any` in public API surfaces
- Generic type parameters on RPC, events, and state APIs
- All exports ship `.d.ts` declarations
